FG-81 — Issue Triage (Win One Thing)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Drop everything that doesn’t move relief today.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Rank issues by (a) signability, (b) pins, (c) remedy clarity. Keep ≤2 issues; park the rest.
	•	📝 Assignment: List your issues; circle the one with cleanest pins + shortest order.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Proceed only on missing harm findings; hold policy debate.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Focus shrinks friction.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A crowded list—only one line highlighted green.

⸻

FG-82 — The Anchor Page (Your Best One Page)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: One page should carry 60% of your case.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Choose a single record page that proves the gap; cite it everywhere (brief, OA, crosswalk).
	•	📝 Assignment: Pick your anchor page and write a 2-sentence why.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Dkt 18 at 2: court ‘did not reach harm.’ That omission drives remand.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: One luminous page > twenty dim ones.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A spotlight on one pinned page.

⸻

FG-83 — Candor With a Point (Admit Then Pivot)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Admit weak facts fast, then show why they don’t change the remedy.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Frame: “Even assuming X, relief follows because Y (pins).” Avoid hedge words; keep the pivot tight.
	•	📝 Assignment: Rewrite a weakness paragraph: admit → pins → remedy.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Even if notice was late by 1 day, the court still skipped harm (Dkt 18:2) → remand 21d.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Candor buys credibility; pins buy outcomes.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A small red flag beside a larger green check.

⸻

FG-84 — Bench Cheat Lines (OA Script in 4 Bars)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Script four micro-lines you can say under pressure.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Ask / Standard / Two pins / Relief—four short bars you can reorder. Memorize, don’t read.
	•	📝 Assignment: Write your four bars in ≤40 words total.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Abuse (wrong test). Pins: Dkt 18:2; Tab 3 p.2. Relief: remand 21d for findings.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Rhythm beats ramble.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Four music bars labeled Ask / Std / Pins / Relief.

⸻

FG-85 — Deadline Cards (Pocket Math)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Carry your clock math as a 4-row card.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Trigger → interval → due → roll-forward; add local cutoff time; staple to every draft.
	•	📝 Assignment: Print a card for your appeal clocks; tape it to your laptop.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Rule 58 08/15 → +30 → 09/14 → weekend → 09/15 11:59 PM.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Visible math prevents invisible misses.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A wallet card with dates and a bold “Due”.

⸻

FG-86 — Authentication First, Argument Second
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Unauthenticated proof isn’t proof.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Add 902(11) certs, headers/EXIF, or clerk stamps; cite the auth page before the content page.
	•	📝 Assignment: For each exhibit, identify the auth pin (page/line) and add it to your crosswalk.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Ex. A cert ¶4 (Tab S-1 p.1); content at Tab 3 p.2.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Provenance persuades.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A lock icon over a page header.

⸻

FG-87 — Relief Scope Paragraph (Don’t Overreach)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Write one sentence that limits who/what/when.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Carve-out non-parties; narrow to ¶ or claim; add sunset and status.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a scope line for your ask.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Stay ¶3 as to parties only; sunset 21 days; status at day 14.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Narrow asks earn “yes.”
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A bracket around a single paragraph line.

⸻

FG-88 — Pre-Drafted Holding Line (What You Want Quoted)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Hand the court the sentence you want in the opinion.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: One neutral line of law (≤18 words) with a clean cite; no facts; paste near your relief.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft your holding line.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Courts must make factor-tied findings before denying preliminary relief. (cite).”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Editors use what’s copy-ready.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A highlighted one-liner dropping into a slip opinion.

⸻

FG-89 — After a Loss: Three Moves in 72 Hours
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Don’t flail; execute a plan.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: (1) Clarify misread line (pin). (2) Admin stay 48–72h (date harm). (3) Notice of intent to seek rehearing with two-pin grounds.
	•	📝 Assignment: Write your 3-move template.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Clarify p.12 n.3; stay ¶3 72h (vendor PO Ex A); rehearing on missing harm findings (Dkt 18:2; Tab 3 p.2).”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Speed + discipline beats despair.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Three small tiles: Clarify / Stay / Rehearing.

⸻

FG-90 — Outcome-First Drafting (Start With the Order)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Draft the order before you draft the brief.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Write the two-line relief and limited-remand block first; make the brief prove those two lines.
	•	📝 Assignment: Paste your order at the top of your draft and write only what proves it.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Vacate & remand 21d for findings (a)–(d); harm-only hearing 20 min; status ≤3 pp.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: If it isn’t in the order, it isn’t in the brief.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A brief being built around a small order card